  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Lenno is our favourite place to get away from it all. It’s in an ideal location right on the shores of the lake that you can’t help but feel relaxed as soon as you arrive. It’s in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/164b7f39f6d74033a2991f5799ebdfa7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/164b7f39f6d74033a2991f5799ebdfa7}" title="Lenno">Lenno</a>, a lovely quiet resort that’s got a handful of lakeside cafés and a tree-lined promenade. It’s off the main tourist trail so you won’t be fighting for a seat next to the water when you stop for lunchtime drink or quick coffee before heading out for the day. It’s the perfect opportunity to enjoy some peace and finish a good book or two.</p>
<p>The hotel is very central and only 20 metres from the ferry point so it’s easy to get out and explore. If you choose to stay for the day then we’d recommend grabbing a spot on the lake-view terrace, which is a great sun trap. It’s next to the pool (normally open mid May to September), which is great for cooling off when the weather gets too warm. Our favourite part of staying here is the dinners. The staff here know their food and how to cook well - you can order all sorts of delicious seasonal dishes from the a la carte menu. There are lots of great local wines to try too.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 2 hours by coach from Milan Malpensa airport.</p>]]></description>
